hink of Pam Bondi as the next attorney general of the United States?</b><br=
/><br/><i>Weissmann</i>: I=E2=80=99ve described this as being cautiously pe=
ssimistic. On the plus side, compared to other proposed nominations, she=E2=
=80=99s somebody who=E2=80=99s had a long career in law enforcement. So it=
=E2=80=99s not like she=E2=80=99s bringing nothing to the table in terms of=
 understanding the craft and what it means to lead an office. On the other =
hand, what I=E2=80=99m missing from her statements [about investigating the=
 investigators of Russiagate, for instance] is any factual predication, and=
 the F.B.I. is trained to understand that you don=E2=80=99t take actions wi=
thout factual predication to justify the activity; the goal is to keep buil=
ding those facts. <br/><br/>Another thing I think is a little bit of a plus=
: She=E2=80=99s not totally shameless. She=E2=80=99s enough of a career
prosecutor to understand that it=E2=80=99s wrong to just investigate everyb=
ody. What remains to be seen is how she conducts herself and what she says =
about that in her confirmation hearing=E2=80=94and then, if she=E2=80=99s c=
onfirmed, how much she is going to take that to heart in her role as attorn=
ey general. <br/><br/><b>When you hear Steve Bannon say the president is al=
so the chief magistrate, is that true?</b><br/><br/><i>Weissmann</i>: It=E2=
=80=99s true in the sense that there=E2=80=99s nothing in the Constitution =
that the Supreme Court has found that requires a president to hold off from=
 telling his attorney general to prosecute certain people and not prosecute=
 others, absent there being selective prosecution claims. That=E2=80=99s so=
mething the president can do. The precedent in the recent Trump immunity de=
cision is all about presidential power and the president=E2=80=99s preclusi=
ve and conclusive power to deal with his Department of Justice. <br/><br/><=
b>What=E2=80=99s your take on Biden=E2=80=99s decision to pardon his
son Hunter, despite having assured the country a lot of times that he would=
n=E2=80=99t do this?</b><br/><br/><i>Weissmann</i>: When looking at the gun=
 charge, as a prosecutor for over 20 years and a defense lawyer for about 1=
0 years, I don=E2=80=99t know of any case that would be prosecuted like Hun=
ter=E2=80=99s was. It seems to me that the only reason Hunter was in that p=
osition is because he=E2=80=99s the son of Joe. If he was Hunter Smith inst=
ead of Hunter Biden, I don&#39;t think he would have been under investigati=
